column5: Right!!that's a longs ways for me to go just to cut ice holes for you,besides that, each hole I cut for you ain't cheap,no freebies,my last name ain't Clark.lol!!
It's only money and to much fun.
I'd like to come back up now,and I would if I was single if you know what I mean.lol

Wasn't planning on fishing today but Wayne Clark texted me early this morning and said I should come over and fish.OK.Got to camp around 9 and fished till 11.Great bite the minute I was setup for about a hour.After that it slowed down but caught one here and there.My hair jig worked great and then I used a lindy rig and that got there attention after they stopped taken the jig.Got some supper in about first 5 min and then fun to play around.
Nice to get a treat and couple of hours of fun.
Nice catch John, looks like a very warm place to ice fish! Ha!
Pretty cozy in there.With our fairly warm Temps we are having I open the windows a bit as even on low temp setting it gets to warm right now.But not complaining.
When u going to stick some lakers??
Soon.Got my sled deck in back of truck.Got ramp out today.Hoping my auger starts today to.But kinda leaning toward getting a electric
Electric are a lot easier on old folks running them.lol
Well it won't start unless I put gas in cylinder.Then quits.Probably needs carb work again.They keep you on your toes.Think primer is toast.
You got a 20 inch bar on your chainsaw,they cut ice!hahaha
